might break me again,

1453
00:57:29,600 --> 00:57:30,320
just like before.

1454
00:57:31,160 --> 00:57:32,560
Just like today's "script."

1455
00:57:32,560 --> 00:57:34,160
Even a married couple

1456
00:57:34,160 --> 00:57:35,720
can go through the seven-year itch.

1457
00:57:36,280 --> 00:57:38,440
Every couple probably

1458
00:57:38,440 --> 00:57:40,520
will have some friction.

1459
00:57:40,520 --> 00:57:42,000
Whether it's emotional,

1460
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:42,840
daily life,

1461
00:57:42,840 --> 00:57:43,840
distance,

1462
00:57:43,840 --> 00:57:44,720
or family,

1463
00:57:44,960 --> 00:57:47,240
all of it can make love hard to sustain.

1464
00:57:47,640 --> 00:57:49,480
After we leave the island,

1465
00:57:49,480 --> 00:57:51,720
these challenges might really show up.

1466
00:57:53,400 --> 00:57:55,200
I just hope you won't feel

1467
00:57:55,200 --> 00:57:56,520
too much pressure,

1468
00:57:56,520 --> 00:57:57,280
like thinking,

1469
00:57:57,280 --> 00:57:58,880
"I can't owe anything to Zhao Enda."

1470
00:57:58,880 --> 00:57:59,960
Even if, in real life,

1471
00:57:59,960 --> 00:58:00,520
you feel

1472
00:58:01,000 --> 00:58:02,680
that spark is gone.

1473
00:58:02,680 --> 00:58:04,160
Maybe Zhao Enda

1474
00:58:04,160 --> 00:58:05,880
isn't the right person

1475
00:58:05,880 --> 00:58:07,120
for your life.

1476
00:58:07,120 --> 00:58:08,320
And that's totally

1477
00:58:08,320 --> 00:58:09,240
okay with me.

1478
00:58:11,800 --> 00:58:12,680
I'm heading back.

1479
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:17,960
Feels like we've talked way too much.

1480
00:58:17,960 --> 00:58:19,520
We keep circling the same topics,

1481
00:58:21,240 --> 00:58:22,320
but never seem to reach

1482
00:58:22,320 --> 00:58:23,120
any conclusion.

1483
00:58:24,720 --> 00:58:25,320
Right?

1484
00:58:25,960 --> 00:58:26,280
Yeah.

1485
00:58:26,280 --> 00:58:26,840
Exactly.

1486
00:58:26,840 --> 00:58:28,560
So let's not force the conclusion.

1487
00:58:31,080 --> 00:58:32,200
Tomorrow's the day for the confession.

1488
00:58:32,200 --> 00:58:33,280
Honestly,

1489
00:58:33,280 --> 00:58:35,880
I feel mostly

1490
00:58:35,880 --> 00:58:36,920
nervous and excited.

1491
00:58:36,920 --> 00:58:38,640
The nervousness comes from

1492
00:58:38,640 --> 00:58:40,360
never having experienced

1493
00:58:41,200 --> 00:58:43,680
such a ceremonial confession before.

1494
00:58:43,680 --> 00:58:45,920
On the other hand,

1495
00:58:46,520 --> 00:58:48,360
I do want a future with her.

1496
00:58:49,000 --> 00:58:50,680
Do you know what we'll do tomorrow?

1497
00:58:51,400 --> 00:58:52,640
Confession balloons.

1498
00:58:52,640 --> 00:58:54,080
Yeah, confession balloons.

1499
00:58:54,600 --> 00:58:56,120
(Reluctant to part)
If there are two buttons in front of you,

1500
00:58:56,120 --> 00:58:56,680
one says confess,

1501
00:58:56,680 --> 00:58:57,520
the other says don't press.

1502
00:58:57,520 --> 00:58:58,400
Which one would you press?

1503
00:58:58,400 --> 00:58:59,320
Of course, I'd confess.

1504
00:59:00,560 --> 00:59:02,200
I hope our story

1505
00:59:02,200 --> 00:59:05,080
doesn't end on this island.

1506
00:59:05,080 --> 00:59:06,720
I hope outside the island,

1507
00:59:06,720 --> 00:59:07,720
we'll have more stories.

1508
00:59:08,320 --> 00:59:09,520
Have you ever

1509
00:59:09,520 --> 00:59:11,320
thought about tomorrow?

1510
00:59:12,040 --> 00:59:13,360
I'd choose to look at you.

1511
00:59:14,240 --> 00:59:14,960
Look at me?

1512
00:59:14,960 --> 00:59:15,240
Yeah.

1513
00:59:15,600 --> 00:59:16,320
Just look at me?

1514
00:59:16,920 --> 00:59:17,440
Yeah.

1515
00:59:18,720 --> 00:59:19,840
When she said that,

1516
00:59:19,840 --> 00:59:21,920
I was really happy.

1517
00:59:21,920 --> 00:59:22,400
But

1518
00:59:23,000 --> 00:59:24,160
I'm still not sure

1519
00:59:24,160 --> 00:59:25,800
if I'll confess tomorrow.

1520
00:59:25,800 --> 00:59:27,120
I've got a lot on my mind.

1521
00:59:27,800 --> 00:59:28,440
It's raining.

1522
00:59:43,300 --> 01:00:00,260
("Live and Love" Release Schedule)

1523
01:00:00,600 --> 01:00:01,560
(Preview)
I'm so nervous.

1524
01:00:01,560 --> 01:00:04,520
Thank you for staying with me these ten days.

1525
01:00:04,520 --> 01:00:07,120
I feel relaxed and happy when I'm with you.

1526
01:00:07,120 --> 01:00:09,160
What I really want to say is

1527
01:00:09,160 --> 01:00:11,080
love can overcome distance.

1528
01:00:11,280 --> 01:00:12,640
I'm really happy

1529
01:00:12,640 --> 01:00:13,920
to have this time with you

1530
01:00:13,920 --> 01:00:15,600
and be part of your life.

1531
01:00:15,640 --> 01:00:16,680
Thank you for being here.

1532
01:00:16,680 --> 01:00:18,320
You gave me the courage

1533
01:00:18,320 --> 01:00:20,280
to fight for the one I love.

1534
01:00:20,880 --> 01:00:22,920
Liu Jiayi, if you're willing to be with me,

1535
01:00:22,920 --> 01:00:25,160
please light this sparkler for me.

1536
01:00:25,200 --> 01:00:26,200
I'm willing to what?

1537
01:00:26,760 --> 01:00:28,680
You're completely stubborn.

1538
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:31,280
I just want an answer.

1539
01:00:31,280 --> 01:00:32,240
You don't have a role.

1540
01:00:32,240 --> 01:00:33,040
I'm sorry.

1541
01:00:34,600 --> 01:00:36,080
Their body language seems...

1542
01:00:36,080 --> 01:00:36,840
Not right.

1543
01:00:36,960 --> 01:00:39,240
I didn't know what you meant.

1544
01:00:39,240 --> 01:00:41,120
Couldn't you hear what I said?

1545
01:00:41,120 --> 01:00:41,960
I heard it.

1546
01:00:41,960 --> 01:00:42,760
Then what exactly

1547
01:00:42,760 --> 01:00:44,400
were you talking about

1548
01:00:44,400 --> 01:00:45,080
later?

1549
01:00:46,080 --> 01:00:49,680
I do want to talk to Jiayi.

1550
01:00:50,320 --> 01:00:51,230
(Pursue love on Balance Island)
Babe,

1551
01:00:51,230 --> 01:00:52,150
(Every Wed. at 12 pm)
are you sleepy?

1552
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:52,960
I'm full,

1553
01:00:52,960 --> 01:00:53,440
babe.

1554
01:00:54,240 --> 01:00:55,080
You gotta add babe

1555
01:00:55,080 --> 01:00:56,160
to everything, huh?

1556
01:00:56,880 --> 01:00:57,600
Yeah, babe.

1557
01:00:57,760 --> 01:00:59,240
What I feel is the show is ending,

1558
01:00:59,240 --> 01:01:00,680
but we're not.

1559
01:01:01,160 --> 01:01:02,560
Of course not.

1560
01:01:02,560 --> 01:01:03,160
Yeah.

1561
01:01:03,160 --> 01:01:03,760
Meeting you

1562
01:01:03,760 --> 01:01:04,240
made me realize

1563
01:01:04,880 --> 01:01:05,800
you're the one.

1564
01:01:06,240 --> 01:01:07,640
But every time you go silent like that,

1565
01:01:07,640 --> 01:01:09,160
(Right in the heart)
it hits me right in the heart.

1566
01:01:10,600 --> 01:01:11,720
I think you're

1567
01:01:11,720 --> 01:01:12,800
really direct,

1568
01:01:12,800 --> 01:01:13,360
and

1569
01:01:13,360 --> 01:01:14,480
straightforward,

1570
01:01:14,480 --> 01:01:15,360
candid.

1571
01:01:15,520 --> 01:01:16,960
Deep down, you have that passion

1572
01:01:16,960 --> 01:01:19,080
and fire I want.

1573
01:01:20,640 --> 01:01:22,450
(Balance Island Special Event)
Hello islanders,

1574
01:01:22,480 --> 01:01:25,040
(On Thu. 12 pm.)
today we'll play four rounds of games.

1575
01:01:25,080 --> 01:01:26,560
Now this is a real game.

1576
01:01:26,560 --> 01:01:27,020
(Crack)

1577
01:01:27,280 --> 01:01:28,120
What's that sound?

1578
01:01:28,120 --> 01:01:29,080
Yang's eating.

1579
01:01:30,640 --> 01:01:31,400
Nice!

1580
01:01:32,280 --> 01:01:33,080
What's so funny?

1581
01:01:33,120 --> 01:01:35,000
How am I supposed to eat these?

1582
01:01:35,000 --> 01:01:36,120
You didn't even wipe it clean,

1583
01:01:36,120 --> 01:01:37,520
and now you're framing me!

1584
01:01:37,520 --> 01:01:38,400
(Seriously?)
I'm leading you to win,

1585
01:01:38,400 --> 01:01:40,080
and you're framing me!

1586
01:01:40,200 --> 01:01:42,200
Your deduction is way off!

1587
01:01:42,200 --> 01:01:44,280
You've lost your judgment again.

1588
01:01:44,280 --> 01:01:45,000
(Shocked)
What?

1589
01:01:45,000 --> 01:01:45,980
(Bestie, look at me.)
Bestie.

1590
01:01:48,960 --> 01:01:49,800
So flirty.

1591
01:01:51,200 --> 01:01:52,200
You look like an idiot.

1592
01:01:52,200 --> 01:01:53,440
I think we've already won.

1593
01:01:53,440 --> 01:01:54,520
Why can't you hold it?

1594
01:01:54,520 --> 01:01:55,560
(Hurry up)
Can you play?

1595
01:01:56,500 --> 01:01:57,820
(Slide and kneel)
